                  </persName>
            . I am drayman to Sir Benjamin Hobhouse and Co., at the brewhouse, in Chiswell-street. On the 8th of October the dray stood at the door of the <placeName id="t18271025-55-crimeloc348">Magpie and Stump public-house</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-55-crimeloc348" type="placeName" value="Magpie and Stump public-house"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18271025-55-crimeloc348" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18271025-55-off344 t18271025-55-crimeloc348"></join>; a man came into the house to me in about ten minutes, and said one of the nose-bags was gone from the horse's head; I went and saw the prisoner with it under his arm, about a quarter of a mile off: he saw me running, and threw the bag away - I caught him, without losing sight of him; he said he did it because he was hungry.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18271025-55-person324">
